      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JANIE BLU (1) has been solid from tough barriers in both starts since a spell, drawing very wide when beaten 4.5m at this circuit and distance first up then coming from the back row for fourth last start. Back in the Brad Hewitt camp and should get every chance from the ace draw. Forgive the latest result of GO COLOUR MY WORLD NZ (2) when he drew very wide at Menangle. Recorded back-to-back placings here prior, one of them from this barrier, so he is much better placed. CAPTAIN MOLLY (5) disappointed as a hot favourite last week but she is better than that so is worth another chance. FLIP A COIN (10) drew wider on this row and worked last start at Bendigo but won two in a row at this venue prior.",
